column1: 0733|thirty-three minutes past seven|He was taken from me
column2: by the inscrutable decree of the Almighty
column3: on the fifth of this month at thirty-three minutes past seven in the morning
column4: and died in peace of an influential attack of the chest - he had been asthmatic of late years

column1:
0733|7:33 A.M.|Wednesday 7:33 A.M.
"You're lucky I love this spot
column2: Vance said, gazing out over the city. Nothing else on the planet could have got me up this early in the morning."
